reviews.review_text: My First I don't what took so long, but I have been looking for this show forever. I can say it was my first - in many ways - but I digress, it was a great show and I remember being at the front of the stage for the second half. The place was steamy and electric...great experience which made me go back again and again. Thanks for making this available....r

Nice Aud sound Since most just want to know how it sounds, not what it was like to actually be there: nice audience recording.  You can hear the crowd etc but the music comes through nice and crisp.  Low bass though.  Worth the DL.

Unfortuntely Overlooked- But very good show Only 2 reviews? Hmm. this Aud is damn good- especially since I was able to torrent a lossless copy of it- the playing throughout the show is crisp and tight- similar more to the spring 77 shows than the early, more exploratory 78 sound.

Stand outs here are a really creative, toe-tapping Jed- which is made all the better by very good slide playing by Bon in counterpoint to Jer's soloing- yep- heard that right- good Bob slide leads- The Music Never Stops is one of the better versions I have ever heard- I think it made the top 10 versions as voted by phantasy tour for their project.

The Scarlet Fire is not earth shattering, nor is the estimated > He's Gone- but they are more than adequate as is the rest of the set. Don't miss out on this show- there is much to like.

One kick Ass show Got to admit this show was one of the best. The Aiko-Aiko was rock-en! What a great show. This recording is great but being at the show is the best way to really understand this show! What a f-en great time! Where can I go to get this stuff now? I would rate this show higher then 5 starts if I could, more like 10 out of 10 starts. Listen closely!

my 3rd show, and a good one  the recording is so so, no bass but the playing is tight, a monster music never stops, worth downloading for this alone , but you also get a fine aiko, a scarlet fire and some more good vibes.
